name: Partial Credit A Cappella
description: Partial Credit, RPI's newest a cappella group, was formed in 2003 with the purpose of providing students with more opportunities to sing. The group is student run with a wide range of musical tastes and practices three times a week. Auditions are held at the beginning of each semester, and the group performs at least once on campus each semester, in addition to singing at other schools and venues. Whether an indie tune, a comedic musical salute, or a unique ballad, Partial Credit takes pride in entertaining others while having fun performing!

name: RPI Ballroom Dance
description: RPI Ballroom offers both social and competitive dance lessons several times weekly in ballroom, rhythm/Latin, and swing dances. We also organize just-for-fun dances as campus events, and our team participates in intercollegiate DanceSport competitions. Anyone can join! All skill levels welcomeâ€”most of our members start from zero. Dances we teach include waltz, tango, foxtrot, rumba, cha-cha, East Coast and West Coast swing, hustle, salsa, merengue, and mambo.

name: Rensselaer Electric Vehicle
description: Rensselaer Electric Vehicle is a club dedicated to creating a prototype electric vehicle for the annual Shell Eco-Marathon competition. Members get hands-on engineering experience, with the opportunity to take ownership of real engineering tasks such as designing and manufacturing electronic and mechanical systems for the vehicle.

name: RPI Tae Kwon Do Club
description: We are a club that meets twice a week at the Mueller Center (or used to before all this) to workout and practice the Korean martial art of Tae Kwon Do. Our group contains members from beginner to black belt rank. Our instructor, 6th dan black belt Chris McEvoy, teaches techniques for self-defense, sparring, traditional forms, general fitness, and board breaking.

name: Art Club
description: Art Club aims to promote creativity for the entire student body, foster an open environment, and encourages art of any and all mediums.

name: Water Polo
description: We are a co-ed water polo club that takes in people of any experience or skill level. Whether you want to train to compete in tournaments with us or be active in a welcoming environment, water polo club is the place for you!

name: Dance Dance Revolution
description: We are a club for playing the rhythm game Dance Dance Revolution, shortened as DDR. DDR is played on a platform by stepping in time to the beat of the music and the corresponding arrow on the screen. We have members of every skill level and welcome anyone who wants to join. We have our own arcade platform and travel to the nearby Dave and Buster's to play on their DDR A machine, the second most recent iteration of DDR.

name: League of Legends
description: Here at RPI's League of Legends club, we enjoy playing our favorite MOBA competitively and casually, and strive to promote a fun gaming atmosphere. We regularly host fun events as well as competitive tournaments. We also engage our members with the professional esports scene. Most of all, we want everyone to have fun, and we will work together to achieve that goal. We hope to provide RPI's students with an abundance of fun League of Legends happenings for years to come.

name: Design Build Fly
description: Design Build Fly (DBF) is an international aircraft design competition in which student teams from universities across the world design, build, and fly a remote controlled aircraft. Each year the American Institute for Aeronautics and Astronautics (AIAA) presents a new design challenge requiring the design of a completely new aircraft.

name: Rensselyrics
description: As RPI's oldest and purplest a cappella group, the Rensselyrics are a co-ed group that sings contemporary music arranged by our members. We perform at various events on campus and in the Troy community, host semesterly invitationals, and participate in local and international competitions.

name: RPI Women's Club Soccer
description: The RPI Women's Club Soccer team aims to play in a competitive and fun environment, without the major time commitment of a varsity sport while still playing at a high level. The team roughly consists of 25 girls. Our main season is from September through October, but practices and games are held throughout the academic year. Practices are held once or twice a week in the evenings and games are usually held on weekend afternoons.

name: Dungeons & Dragons Club
description: Our main focus is on D&D, but we're also involved in TTRPGs and RPGs in general. We use our Discord server to have meetings, discuss all things D&D, and hopefully run some contests and other events throughout the semester.

name: HackRPI
description: HackRPl is the student organizations that hosts the annual intercollegiate hackathon at Rensselaer Polytechnic Institute. We are a collective of RPI students who share a passion for exploring the bounds of computer science and pushing the limits of what students can do. Fall 2020 will be our seventh hackathon and through our experiences, we have seen what makes hackathons so awesome and what we can do to take the hackathon experience to the next level. Our goal is to inspire and challenge innovators, developers, creators, and entrepreneurs in New Yorkâ€™s Tech Valley and beyond. We will help attendees develop their skills, explore new technologies, and turn their curiosities and visions into opportunities. Staying true to our mantra â€œwhy not code the world?â€, we strive to solve challenging real world problems in order to generate tangible outcomes. ln our six years, we dedicated significant efforts towards reaching this goal. We have dedicated ourselves to ensuring that HackRPl meets our own high expectations; admittedly, we cannot achieve greatness on our ownâ€”we need your help

name: Rifle Club
description: Whether you want to become a shooting competitor or just learn the basics to target shooting, this is the club for you. No previous experience necessary! Using the best in current air rifle technology andone-on-one coaching, you can come to our on-campus range and develop your shooting skills as often as you'd like. This club is all about self-discipline and personal training to improve your skills from the ground up. All new members will receive full instruction on safety and technique. Anyone can do it; all you need is determination.

name: Active Minds
description: Active Minds seeks to start open conversations about mental health and mental illness with a focus on student issues. We aim to educate students about mental health and available resources and to bring attention to the issues prevalent in our community. We host weekly meetings and larger events, such as our annual Stronger Than The Stigma event, and collaborate with other organizations on- and off-campus to reach a wide audience in an effort to end the stigma surrounding mental illness.

name: RPI Spaceflight Society
description: The RPI Spaceflight Society shall exist to promote the exploration and development of space, through educating people about the benefits of space, by supporting a network of interested students, by providing an opportunity for members to develop their leadership skills, and by inspiring people through involvement in space-related projects.

name: Rensselaer Astrophysical Society (RAS)
description: The Rensselaer Astrophysical Society (RAS) allows students to pursue their interest in astronomy. The society works in conjunction with the physics department to maintain the Hirsch Observatory atop the Science Center. Students are trained in the use of observatory and the Society's various telescopes, then placed on the observatory key list. Once on the key list, members can use the observatory at any time. The club also helps run Saturday night public observing sessions between February and November of each year.

name: Cru RPI
description: Cru is a caring community passionate about connecting people to Jesus Christ. We hold weekly small group and large group meetings; more detailed information can be found at crurpi.org.

name: Rensselaer Crew Club
description: With Rensselaer Crew Club, anyone can learn how to row! Experienced rowers and absolute beginners are welcome to join! The club practices on the Hudson River, in boats of 4 or 8 people, with races taking place on weekends.

name: Colleges Against Cancer
description: We fundraise for the American Cancer Society and plan the Relay for Life event on campus.

name: Alpha Delta Phi Society
description: We are an inclusive and interdisciplinary national Greek organization that specializes in cultivating literary and artistic endeavors across college campuses.The Society provides students with distinct leadership experiences, scholarship opportunities, and a support network that lasts beyond a Siblingâ€™s undergraduate education.

name: The Rusty Pipes
description: The Rusty Pipes is a co ed acapella group here at RPI! We perform at events on campus, and locally in Troy and Albany as well as participate in competitions around the Northeast.

name: Conversation Corner and Mandarin Club
description: We are in intercultural club where Mandarin speakers come together to practice, play games, and learn about each other's cultures. The club is open to all and split about evenly between native speakers and people learning Chinese.

name: RPI Circle K
description: RPI Circle K is an international collegiate service organization that focuses on developing the leadership skills of its members, while establishing a sense of community and fellowship. Our large annual fundraisers (i.e. Pie Sales, Haunted House, and Iron Chef Cooking Competition) and additional service activities impact not only the Troy community, but also national and international charities, allowing our members to connect and work with other service-driven students worldwide!

name: RPI Dance Team
description: RPI Dance Team is a group of students who share a love for dance and performance. We promote school spirit by performing jazz, pom, and hip hop numbers at home football games, home basketball games, and other school events. We also compete annually in the spring.

name: Global Medical Brigades
description: Rensselaer Polytechnic Institute is a chapter of Global Medical Brigades, an international movement of students and medical professionals working alongside local communities and staff to implement sustainable health systems. We work in remote, rural, and under resourced communities in Honduras, Panama, Nicaragua and Ghana who would otherwise have limited to no access to health care. Each community receives a brigade every 3 to 4 months where hundreds of patients are provided access to healthcare and volunteers deliver public health workshops. Electronic patient records are collected for future visitations and to monitor overall community health trends. In conjunction with our Medical Program, Global Brigades also supports communities with economic development, sanitation and clean water projects, and uniquely implements these programs in a holistic model to meet a communityâ€™s health and economic goals. Our model systematically builds community ownership and collaboratively executes programs with the end goal of sustainably evolving to a relationship of impact monitoring.

name: The RPI Players
description: The RPI Players is a student-run theatre company open to all RPI students, faculty, staff, and the greater Capital Region community. The RPI Players is one of the oldest theatre troupes in the area, and has staged over 300 shows in it's nearly 90 seasons. The RPI Players produce between three and six shows per year, and call the RPI Playhouse their home. Often, the Players will collaborate with a variety of performing arts organizations on campus and in the community. Discord link: https://discord.gg/mfzZxcZgCA

name: RPI-Sage Hillel
description: Hillel is the Jewish student organization serving the students of Rensselaer Polytechnic Institute and the Russell Sage College Troy campus.

name: RPI Society of Women Engineers
description: The Society of Women Engineers at Rensselaer Polytechnic Institute provides its members with the ideal engineering and college experience. SWE is a unique opportunity to meet other women on campus with similar interests as your own, give and receive support, and create a network of friends. However, you do not need to be an engineer or even a female to join! We have many events and opportunities which can benefit any major or gender at RPI, including corporate guests and interview/resume training, as well as fun social events to take a study break.

name: Rensselaer Model Railroad Society
description: The Rensselaer Model Railroad Society constructs, maintains, and operates a historically accurate scale model railroad layout. This layout is regarded as one of the best in the United States and has received public acclaim and media coverage over the many years of its existence.

name: Club Racquetball
description: This is a laid-back club where you can come learn and play some racquetball. No previous experience is necessary, and all necessary equipment can be provided. We have completely optional practices four times a week, as well as the option to attend five different tournaments (against other schools) through out the year.

name: RPI Club Tennis
description: The club tennis team competes against a variety of schools against the northeast. Our team is comprised of players with a variety of skill levels. As a club sport, the time commitment is less than a varsity sport. We practice 2-3 times per week in the fall and spring, and once per week at a local tennis club during the winter.

name: The Forge
description: The Forge is a student-run makerspace that provides a collaborative environment for students at Rensselaer to explore rapid prototyping and design. Members have access to a wide range of equipment including but not limited to various 3D printers, a laser cutter, and an electronics workstation. All students regardless of their major are able to become members and attend the workshops, design competitions, and outreach events hosted every semester.

name: Pep Band
description: Pep Band plays contemporary and hype music at all home hockey and football games, and travels a few times a semester. We also play charity events, marathons, admissions events, you name it!

name: Union Show Techs
description: UST provides the RPI community with high-quality sound and lighting reinforcement, and to give members an opportunity to use and learn about lighting and sound equipment in a fun and social environment.

name: Winter Carnival
description: The winter carnival club spends the fall semester planning a carnival for the spring. During these meetings we discuss everything from vendors, gifts, carnival games, to food!

name: Design for America
description: Do you like ethical design and STEM? We're looking for anyone of any experience level and academic background to join the Rensselaer Studio of Design for America (DFA). We are one of 37 college studios fostering design thinking and innovation in their members across the United States. DFA grows your understanding of design, exposes you to a network of talented students and alumni, and provides resources to put your creativity towards helping others. By joining DFA's welcoming and inclusive community, you will make fast friends, lifelong connections, and have a great deal of fun, all while improving your design skills.

name: Bwenzi
description: Bwenzi is an outreach club whose initiative is to take on the global issues of health and education. We are an alliance of students that care enough to look beyond borders and empower other students to do good. Currently, we are focused on helping three villages in Malawi, Africa.

name: Rensselaer Running Club
description: Rensselaer Running Club is open to students of all ability and commitment levels who share a passion for running. Students will be able to participate in workouts, road races, charity events, and additional team-building activities of their choosing.

name: RPI Humans vs Zombies
description: Our club is dedicated to the tag like game of Humans vs Zombies. Using our massive arsenal of nerf blasters we fight endless wave of zombies across the entire campus and attempt to not succumb to the horde. Due to COVID we will be focusing on recreating the HvZ experience online within video games. We also plan on showing off nerf modding techniques and will hopefully expand into smaller scale in-person games as the year progresses.
